         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">20/7/95 ¶  ¶ It interests me much, dear Mr Tyson, that you have an Acacia on  ¶ limestone ¶  soil, which exudes much  ¶ Gum ¶ . Kindly send me leaves &amp; flowers and if possible also  ¶ pods ¶  (fruits)...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">95.07.20</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Isaac Tyson</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">MS 58 (044) MUE, WA Herbarium, Perth,</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">Bot names to check.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>20/7/95</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It interests me much, dear Mr Tyson, that you have an Acacia on <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">limestone</hi>
               </seg> soil, which exudes much <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Gum</hi>
               </seg>. Kindly send me leaves &amp; flowers and if possible also <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">pods</hi>
               </seg> (fruits) so that the name of <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">this</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Gum</hi>
               </seg>-yielder may be ascertained</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Do you use any Acacia-barks there for tanning? Does any of your Eucalypts yield much Kino?</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your notes on Canavalia Curum,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">check the commas and the insertion here.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> Panicumopestalute &amp;c Cotton-Bud wheat &amp;c are very important, but it would be still further necessary to learn, experimentally, whether any of these plants will succeed <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">without</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">irri</hi>
               </seg>gation in your clime</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>If you find that your herds and flocks feed on any particular indigenous herbage with predilection, will you send a little of it, so that I can introduce such plants under your honored name into the next edition of the Select plants.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Always regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
         </div>
      </body>
   </text>
